TITLE: US-backed Kurdish forces detain 300 ISIS fighters in al-Hol camp raid operation
SUMMARY: CENTCOM has focused on the Syrian refugee camp al-Hol as a significant target for ISIS recruitment and indoctrination due to the severe conditions present at the camp.

TITLE: US lifts Cyprus arms embargo, Turkey claims decision will lead to 'arms race' in Mediterranean
SUMMARY: The U.S. embargo started in 1987 as an effort to allegedly help re-unify the island following a Turkish invasion that created a breakaway state and years of fierce combat.

TITLE: 6.9 magnitude earthquake rocks Taiwan, triggers Tsunami alarm in Japan
SUMMARY: A 6.9 magnitude earthquake struck the island of Taiwan on Sunday, reportedly killing one and injuring 79. First responders are on the scenes of collapsed buildings and bridges.

TITLE: Azerbaijan dismisses Nancy Pelosi as 'Armenian propaganda' after she condemns Azeri attacks
SUMMARY: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi condemned Azerbaijan's attacks on Armenia on Sunday, prompting anger from Azerbaijan, which derided her statement as "Armenian propaganda."

TITLE: UK invites Taiwan to sign queenâ€™s condolence book in symbolic China rebuke
SUMMARY: The U.K. acknowledged Taiwan's status as a self-governed country by inviting its representative in The UK to sign Queen Elizabeth II's condolence book on Sunday.

TITLE: Retired Florida doctor travels to Ukraine to help infants and newborns impacted by Russia's invasion
SUMMARY: A retired Florida doctor returned to work, traveling thousands of miles to Ukraine to help newborns and infants impacted by the country's ongoing war with Russia.

TITLE: Biden arrives in UK for queen's funeral; Liz Truss meeting postponed
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden arrived in London on Saturday to pay respects to Queen Elizabeth II at her funeral and to attend a formal state reception hosted by King Charles III.

TITLE: US-backed fighters rescue tens of thousands of women and children in raid on ISIS al-Hol camp
SUMMARY: The U.S.-backed Kurdish-led Syrian Democratic Forces led a 24-day raid on a refugee camp in Northern Syria, resulting in the rescue of thousands of women and children from IS fighters.

TITLE: Chinese currency still depicting Mao Zedong indicates 'leftist murderers get a pass' in history
SUMMARY: Gordon Chang says the depiction of Mao Zedong on the Chinese Renminbi indicates that 'leftist murderers get a pass' for their crimes.

TITLE: Russian businessmen keep dying under mysterious circumstances since Putin invaded Ukraine: report
SUMMARY: Some of the deaths may relate to a corruption investigation into Russian gas company Gazprom, but the number of deaths has only increased during the invasion of Ukraine.
